In [140]:
# Setting features data X (independent variables) and target variable y (dependent variable / label)
X = features_scaled_df # not include 'class' column
y = df_clear['class']

# Data split for 80% training model (training set) and 20% testing model (test set)
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, train_size=0.8, random_state=42)

# Logistic Regression
logreg = LogisticRegression(solver='liblinear', max_iter=1000)
logreg.fit(X_train, y_train)


# Support Vector Machine（SVM)
svm = SVC(kernel='rbf', probability=True)
svm.fit(X_train, y_train)

# Random Forest 
rf = RandomForestClassifier(n_estimators=100, random_state=42)
rf.fit(X_train, y_train)

Step 6: Build a predictive system to verify that the model built is able to predict the patient’s Parkinson’s disease with one instance of the dataset.¶

In [146]:
# Defind function to predict Parkinson's disease
def predict_parkinson(input_data):
    # Convert to DataFrame (assuming input_data is a dictionary or a single row in CSV)
    df_dataframe = pd.DataFrame([input_data])

    # Drop 'id' column if it exists
    if 'id' in df_dataframe.columns:
        df_dataframe = df_dataframe.drop(columns=['id'])
    
    # Make sure the columns are correct
    df_dataframe = df_dataframe[features_scaled_df.columns]

    # Normalize features
    X_std = scaler.transform(df_dataframe)

    # Wrap back into DataFrame, preserving column names
    X_std_df = pd.DataFrame(X_std, columns=df_dataframe.columns)

    # Predict three models
    pred_logreg = logreg.predict(X_std_df)[0]
    pred_svm = svm.predict(X_std_df)[0]
    pred_rf = rf.predict(X_std_df)[0]

    # probability of PD using three models
    prob_logreg = logreg.predict_proba(X_std_df)[0][1] if hasattr(logreg, "predict_proba") else None
    prob_svm = svm.predict_proba(X_std_df)[0][1] if hasattr(svm, "predict_proba") else None
    prob_rf = rf.predict_proba(X_std_df)[0][1] if hasattr(rf, "predict_proba") else None

    return {
        "Logistic Regression": {"prediction": pred_logreg, "probability": prob_logreg},
        "SVM": {"prediction": pred_svm, "probability": prob_svm},
        "Random Forest": {"prediction": pred_rf, "probability": prob_rf}
    }

# Using a test set to predict Parkinson's disease with three models
sample = X_test.iloc[0].to_dict() # X_test is the processed test set
results = predict_parkinson(sample)

# Display the prediction results
print("Prediction Parkinson's disease results with three models:")
for model, res in results.items():
    print(f"{model}: Prediction = {'PD' if res['prediction']==1 else 'Healthy'}, Probability = {res['probability']:.2f}")

Prediction Parkinson's disease results with three models:
Logistic Regression: Prediction = Healthy, Probability = 0.00
SVM: Prediction = PD, Probability = 0.50
